caption: Amazing restaurant! Great chef and everyone is super kind! You always feel at home ☺️ also, the distance between tables is safe and everyone complies with the social distance measures. Nice terrace outside with heating available. Would recommend 150%!!!
They food here is so tasty here and they have a wonderful menu selection. I highly recommend you try them out when you get the moment.
One of the best meals I've ever had. Everything was incredible- food, drinks, dessert- and the service and atmosphere were exceptional. Highly recommended!!
Delicious food and excellent service

It took us a while to get a reservation but it was worth the wait! This restaurant is outstanding - very fresh, creative and delicious food, beautifully displayed; wonderful service; open kitchen with wood-burning hearth (provides great entertainment!); very nice vibe. We loved every dish we had: catfish dip, scallop crudo, farm egg, flank steak, glazed carrots (amazing!), cornbread, apple crumble, and more. The sommelier recommended a great bottle of wine. We loved our experience and will be back soon! Thank you to the amazing chef and staff at the Dabney.

Food was alright, Covid precautions were over the Top!!! There are many other restaurants in DC that have better food for the same price, nothing out of the ordinary here. However due to the fact that they take their Covid precautions to the extreme, will not come back. I could not enjoy my dinner, because every time I was in the middle of enjoying a dish, a waiter would come around to bring something to the table and ask you to mask up. This is a pre-course dinner so they keep bringing dishes, and drinks so imagine having to put n a take off your mask at least 20 times during your dinner.  There are plenty of other restaurants in DC that allow you to safely have dinner during Covid without going over the top. This is not one of them. Also, even though they are so cautious about Covid, one of the waiters kept touching his mask ( I assume the N-95 mask was not fitted correctly on him, hence he had to constantly fiddle with it)  which defeats the purpose of wearing one if you constantly touch it, and the pour water or bring out my food after touching your mask.
Food was extremely delicious. The snacks each complimented each other. I got the crab, which was luscious and well cooked.
Without a doubt one of my favorite and best restaurants in DC.
Thank you for this fantastic food and staff

Shared a great dinner with friends last evening. Our server Steven was a delight.  Dining room was full, but staged at 25% per current Covid19 restrictions.  Everyone was wearing masks. We all felt safe and really enjoyed a wonderful, unrushed experience.  Service, food and wine were exceptional.
Excellent food, service and ambience. Had the rockfish as main course and it was delicious.
Great overall experience. The staff was incredible and very knowledgeable. The food was unique and flavorful. My fiancé and I will definitely be back there.

Food and drinks were very good. The ambiance was a 1 however. Most of the staff were friendly. A few were super frigid.  You go to these places for the full experience and unfortunately this place failed to deliver on that front. They took covid awareness to a different level. Just to note we are very conciousness  of this ourselves and take every precaution. Every time a server came around you had to mask up. In fact we were told at seating that while we are not drinking or eating we should mask up while sitting at the table.  You literally  have to keep.your mask on one hand all night. After a while it really got out of hand when you are on a  5 meal course. They said that was DC rules which I think was exaggerated.  In the past weeks we had visited  Bresca, Nobu and  Blue Duck  and we didn't experience the same policy.  They should advertise their policy and let people know ahead of time of this when making reservations. It may seem like a small thing. But trust me  when I say it was honestly annoying. Make sure to take a disposable mask otherwise you'll smell your dinner for a long time as many times we masked up. I don't think we ll go back again, perhaps when covid is all done with we'll give it another try .

We were so pleasantly surprised by the tasting meal. It gave us so many different flavors and chances to try things we may not have ordered on our own. It was our anniversary and we were visiting from New York and they went out of their way to make the whole night special. The manager and our waiter were so kind and really made us feel comfortable and welcome. Amazing meal.

Amazing restaurant! Great chef and everyone is super kind! You always feel at home ☺️ also, the distance between tables is safe and everyone complies with the social distance measures. Nice terrace outside with heating available. Would recommend 150%!!!
Prefixed 4 meal course.  Amazing flavor profile and variety. Their drinks are to die for too.  Service is just beyond amazing
Fantastic! Not to be missed.

What an evening. The Dabney did not disappoint. A belated Valentine’s Day dinner, we enjoyed their now standard price fixed menu at $85/person. We elected for the lobster tail and corn bread for a minimal upcharge. The drinks - I got the Virginia Old Fashioned and @rachel.mouring the marigold - we well done. We both got the beef short rib. Excellent dining experience. Excellent staff. Well done. Be sure to ask for a table by the fire pits if you enjoy watching the kitchen at work.

Don't waste your money..  Especially if you are a vegetarian.  For $85 per person- they will offer you one of their appetizers: roasted vegetables as an entree and that is it, even if your whole table is vegetarian.  After calling and asking about options, they didn't get back to me until the next day (day of) the reservation and charged $35 a person for canceling after offering the above and only option.  I  lose respect for restaurants that care more about money than their patrons.. and found this entire situation straight up appalling.  As someone in the business and knowing how Covid has affected all of us (especially restaurants) it's obvious they are hurting for money and its going to hurt their reputation.
Great atmosphere amazing food
great food and atmosphere
nice
great place to eat
Amazing meal! From food to service to atmosphere, all superb!!! Thank you for a wonderful meal and experience.
My boyfriend and I loved this place. Wonderful service

My husband and I had an amazing experience at The Dabney. The service was great and the ambiance was perfect for us (formal but still warm and inviting). We both liked the food better than the food we had at a Michelin 3 star restaurant. It was flavorful and fresh. I already asked my husband to try and re-create the celery root soup. Highly recommend!

Went here for a birthday dinner in January of 2021. The entire staff was VERY conscious of COVID protocols, which while some could look at as annoying (we had to put our masks on every time someone approached the table, even if you were mid-bite), but I chose to look at as a restaurant so dedicated to serving great food and keeping staff employee that they were willing to do anything! In a post- COVID world, this restaurant will continue to put patrons and their staff first which is a great quality!  The food was phenomenal and was honestly better than anticipated! The ambiance was so cute and fun and made the night feel really special. I can’t wait to go back again!!!!
Dined here with a friend, who lives in DC. Great restaurant

Food was extremely delicious. The snacks each complimented each other. I got the crab, which was luscious and well cooked. Decided to go with the chicken soup on a cold night and oh my gosh... It was the best chicken soup I have ever had. It was so vibrant with the greens and incredibly earthy, tied together with the warm broth. Dessert was also soooooo good!
The Dabney is great at taking simple ingredients and bringing out a ton of flavor. Their bread and butter alone could be my entire meal and I’d be satisfied.

Food was extremely delicious. The snacks each complimented each other. I got the crab, which was luscious and well cooked. Decided to go with the chicken soup on a cold night and oh my gosh... It was the best chicken soup I have ever had. It was so vibrant with the greens and incredibly earthy, tied together with the warm broth.
Got the to-go dinner for two and... woah. The pork belly was the best my partner and I have had. And the plum pudding was incredible! 10/10 would recommend The Dabney's to-go dinner.
Phenomenal experience!! My wife and I loved our time here and the food was delicious.
A must for a post-covid date, celebration, special occasion.  Incredible food and the ambiance is as good as it gets.
We’ve been coming here for years and it is consistently our favorite restaurant in DC. Always awesome food, service, and atmosphere.

I didn’t dine in so I can’t review the service, but I got the holiday carry-out meal and WOW. First off, I ordered for two people and the menu was for two meals, so I expected four meals, essentially. We got 6 large meals. And every item was delicious. I especially enjoyed the charred Brussels sprouts as they had some kind of nut and carried an crunch, the sweet potato rolls with sesame seeds, and the prime rib. The HUGE prime rib. The instructions for reheating were easy to follow, and the presentation was visually stunning, even replated. Also, order the Dabnog. For goddess’ sake, order the dabnog. I don’t even LIKE eggnog and I drank this three nights in a row. It’s hands down the best eggnog I’ve ever had. Pricey...but so, so worth it.
Interesting flavor

We got the special twice during our stay. The catfish sliders are sooooo good! Each dish we tried we loved! This is the best food experience I have ever had and next time I am in DC I will try it again. The menus change frequently which is so amazing! Food is creative and finished beautifully.
Went there preCovid Amazing food and vibe.

Pros: Great service and mostly great atmosphere. Had to sit on the covered patio with a space heater that kept us warm for the most part.  Annoying when staff asked us to put our masks on while sitting at the table just for them to put our food down. Waiter was friendly and attentive.  Cons: way overpriced for the “sample size” portions of overly pretentious names dishes. Could easily have got way better food and saved the $300. May not have a sophisticated enough palate for here and the food was delicious but just not a good value for your money.  I’d choose elsewhere first.
Michelin starred cuisine, fine service, a lovely setting. Save up, it is worth a pilgrimage for all food lovers.
Nothing is disappointing here. Enough said.

We got the special twice during our stay. It is $45 a person for a whole dinner with dessert. The catfish sliders are sooooo good! Each dish we tried we loved! This is the best food experience I have ever had and next time I am in DC I will try it again. The menus change frequently which is so amazing!
Excellent food & amazing service!

When I’m a millionaire I’m going to eat at The Dabney every single day. The food is outstanding, although much much better at the restaurant than to-go. The only miss on the pre fixe menu is the rockfish. $75/pp might seem steep to you but honestly we walked away thinking we got a great value. There are two bonus items you get on top of the menu (bread at the beginning and bon bons after dessert) plus my malted chocolate ice cream dessert was literally as big as a softball. It has 1 Michelin star but honestly just as good as 2 star pineapples and pearls.

Incredible meal. Four courses, served over the course of about an hour and a half. The service was exceptional and the food was out of this world. Ended up getting all the snacks (they're all included), the butternut squash on the fire as an appetizer, the chicken and dumplings (their unique take with TONS of fall root vegetables), and the apple crumble for dessert. And it was my birthday, so they put a candle on my dessert and brought us complimentary prosecco to celebrate with. Truly one of the best meals I've had in the last decade or so. The ambiance is wonderful, too. Would give more than 5 stars if that was possible.
Great experience. The flavors were amazing. The flame and the grill were amazing!
The food is always good! High price tag but I always left full and happy. Charming atmosphere :)

Smoked Catfish to go?? I took a risk and decided to try the Smoked Catfish to go - it's always been one of my favorite entries for eating inside of Dabney. However, since COVID, I've been doing a lot of to-go from many of my favorite restaurants. I've been completely disappoint. So I was a little hesitant when ordering my favorite dish from Dadney. But I was craving it, so I took my chances and ordered it anyway. I'm glad I took the risk, well worth the reward. The same in-restaurant smoked catfish. The only difference I was eating it from my couch.  Love you guys!!
The food here is always good. Take out even better. keep up the amazing work
Their new breakfast menu is as good as their dinner!  I've never had a better donut. I come here frequently for both breakfast and dinner, and it's always delicious.
Great experience and food!
Ordered take out for a birthday dinner. The food was amazing and still looked beautiful even in to-go containers! Perfect reheating instructions and great quality all around.
Always incredible-delicious food, perfect portions, fabulous staff, and such a great atmosphere. Would recommend to all seeking a classic, fine dining experience in the nation’s capital!

Whether it be for dinner or now breakfast, whether it be dine-in (man do I miss that!) or take-out during COVID, this place goes above and beyond my wildest expectations in terms of what a neighborhood restaurant can be in terms of both the food and the service.  They absolutely deserve all of the praise they get (and probably more).  Fantastic job to the entire Dabney Team.
Brunch to-go didn't disappoint. Donuts are a must.
Fabulous food - "hyper-local" and incredibly fresh. Highly recommend.

First of all, we were really happy to know that the Dabney is still open during COVID. We want to support local businesses and help them survive this pandemic, so we decided to order  takeout from this famous restaurant. We drove 45 minutes into the city to pick up our order on a rainy day. After the drive, I really needed to use the restroom because I am 6 month pregnant. (When you are pregnant, you cannot control when you really need to use the restroom.) We asked if we could use the restroom as a paying customer and we were told no. I understand this is all because of COVID but I cannot support a business that doesn't want support their patrons. Also, it's not like they are doing  takeout only, they take reservations and offer outdoor dining services. I hope they are not treating us differently because we are Asians. We are truly  disappointed for eagerly supporting a business that doesn't care about its clients.
Good food and atmosphere
(Translated by Google) They have good service  (Original) Tienen buen servicio
Great atmosphere and great food. The use of fires in cooking adds to the ambiance as well as the flavor of the food.

We ordered takeout for my birthday during quarantine and everything was amazing. I even had the banana pudding the next day and it was still perfect. But i'm mainly writing this review to talk about the catfish slider. I am usually meehhhhh about fish. I have never ordered fish for myself off a menu. I would order this catfish slider over a burger. It's that good.

Great pickup process!  Easy to park and grab.  Sweet Potato Roll with Chicken 4/5 Summer Cucumber Gazpacho 5/5 Grilled Mahi 5/5 Raspberry Mille Feuille 5/5 Little cookie treat.  I might have wanted a little bit more quantity but I am a little chubby too.  Everything was fresh and delicious without any complaints.  The gazpacho was the shining course out of then all.

All of the dishes were thoughtfully composed and had a perfect balance of flavors. We dined in the summer so we also got to experience the fresh produce that was being used. The highlights for dinner included the broccoli & crab dish and grilled quail. We also enjoyed the cornbread which was very savory and crispy.
Most certainly worth the wait, if you didn't already make reservations. The ambiance and decor is beautiful. The food and service are well deserving of their Michelin Star.

Great food and wine.  We really enjoyed the tuna and rockfish dishes. The steak was very good too, but I'm not sure it was worth the $100 price tag. We had exceptional service and the wait staff was always available to answer questions or refill our drinks. Overall it was a great experience.

UPDATE: 4/26/2020- We did the pick up service, since dining in is not an option at all restaurants. We had an excellent meal at such a reasonable price for a Michelin starred restaurant. The snack, the starter, the entree, all excellent. The sweet potato roll with catfish was like a Chic-fil-A sandwich on a Sunday, a rare treat only to be had due to tragedy. The chicken, was finger licking good, and the dessert was like a nice fancy brownie cake. -----  It was 5-6 stars up until the entree. Unfortunately, like many places the apps way outshine the entrees the way Beyonce outshines the rest of Destiny's Child. If we had just stopped at the apps we would still be on a cloud. We ordered the Sweet Potato Roll with Pork Belly, the Poached Farm Egg, the Buttermilk Biscuit, the swordfish and the grilled pork. I want to go back again just for the Buttermilk Biscuit, for it is divine, egg, foie gras, a thin sliver of ham and the maple.....heaven on a plate. The Poached Farm Egg, also excellent, creamy, with pork. Then after that, things went to the land of 'just okay'. The swordfish may as well have been tofu because it didn't seem to have a taste of its own and the other things on the plate just didn't seem to go with each other. The grilled pork was also just okay. The dessert, as others have mentioned, leave much to be desired. We had the blondie as it was the only thing that seemed to promise chocolate. It was okay sort of. Not bad, just more of a let down. The tiny pecan cookies that came with our bill were way better. Service was good. Atmosphere was charming, and after about 6:30 you must speak with a raised voice. We will return, the Buttermilk Biscuits are calling my name.
Amazing take out during these times. I love this place
Gourmet take out. The food is an experience, not just a meal. The ingredients are a perfect balance and blend of textures, flavors, and smells.

Quite possibly the best meal of my life. From the time we arrived the the time we left everything was perfect (other than them selling out of oyster sliders). The staff was incredibly attentive, friendly and knowledgeable. Every course was immaculate but the star of the show was definitely the previously mentioned sliders. The cocktails were equally delicious and complex. Overall it was everything I expected from a Michelin starred restaurant and more. At about $100 a person with drinks for my party it really wasn’t a bad deal for a very memorable night either.

The catfish sliders are amazing and worth the trip (at $5 each, they are worth the trip and a great appetizer). The catfish is crispy, yet melts in your mouth with the right toppings, sauce and bun to create the ideal bite.  Service and ambiance are great. I sat at the bar and the service was attentive and friendly, without rushing. I love the decor, with the fireplace, open oven, brick and plants.  I had a "smoky" tequila cocktail that didn't taste smoky and wasn't worth $14. It left me craving mescal from a nearby spot.  The chicken and dumplings left me feeling mixed. The broth has a great depth of flavor and the chicken is tasty (some pieces are a bit big for a bite). I also liked the dumplings, but you have to go on a treasure hunt to find them at the bottom of the pot. The big miss is the addition of raw winter vegetables. I love carrots in soup, but these were too crunchy (no texture benefit) and served as a distraction, not an addition. Cook the carrots longer, add more dumplings, and this dish is a home run.
I ordered 4 things off the menu and they were pretty hit or miss. Some interesting combinations. I would come back, but I don't think this would ever be a go-to spot. Service was a 4.
Such good food and service!

2020-3-7 Update: This was my wife and my 2nd time to The Dabney and it did not disappoint. The meal always starts with the catfish sliders...a must. My wife said, "if you're not putting any extra sauce on them, they must be good" and they are indeed. Besides the sliders, we purposely tried to have different items than we did the 1st time. I got pics of everything we had this time to make it easier for our next visit lol. Our waitress recommended ordering 4-6 items and our consensus is that's too much for us. The sliders themselves are a pretty solid start, but if you take the table bread (which is also delicious) and drinks, we personally think it's too much seeing that you want to get dessert in too ;-) The star of the night: braised short rib. Fork tender and so delicious and pairs perfectly with the creamed potatoes. Initially I was disappointed not to see the Butterscotch pie on the menu, but not for long as the Apple crumble may have taken the dessert crown. Good food, energetic setting, & great service. Look forward to our next visit.  1st review: Dabney was sooooo good! We will definitely be going back to this place. It's a nice place, great wait staff, good drinks, and really good food. We tried a lot of things and they were all good. Also, the Butterscotch pie is a great dinner ender. Can't wait to go back...but get your reservations in.
Great ambience, great food

The Dabney specializes in small plates and unique dishes with interesting combinations. However, somehow it all works together and becomes a perfect marriage of flavors in your mouth. You wont go wrong with the catfish sliders, which are absolutely delicious a must try that leave you wanting more. The broccoli crab, flank steak and potato salad. Each dish is presented with a nice little introduction that gets you excited about getting ready to taste your meal.
Food and service were amazing. There were at least 5 vegetarian options.

Nice ambiance and decor. Staff was polite and helpful.The open  wood fire gives the place a nice feel to it, but the food was  average at best. Out 5 dishes I ordered, one dish was a good surprise:The fried oysters and veggies. However everything else was bland and very little originality from dish to dish. At last my dessert was frozen in the middle! I had enough. I will not visit again.

I decided to treat myself at the end of a conference, and boy did I! Everything was fabulous. I sat at the bar and the bartender did not steer me wrong with my choices. The food was delectable from the start with the bread and butter, all the way to the buttermilk sauce and greens with the sugar toads. I cannot recommend this place enough.
Superb Dining.  Everything is very good.

We were traveling from Philadelphia and had the pleasure of dining at The Dabney! Food was incredible! Also, the service was amazing. Blake really made us feel welcomed and wouldn’t have had the experience we did with out him as our waiter. Highly recommend stopping by for a delicious dinner!!
Great atmosphere and great food. The use of fires in cooking adds to the ambiance as well as the flavor of the food.
Great experience, cool atmosphere, great flavor.
love this place
Delicious food and great atmosphere!

There's no way to adequately describe how incredible The Dabney is! The catfish sliders and catfish dip were the best! And we also loved the oysters, scallop crudo, foie gras, greens and  hummingbird cheese. As visitors from SC we were excited to see the chef, Jeremiah Langhorne. Loved!

Reservation system is cheating! Tried reserving on the web site for the st.Valentines day. Picked the time available, when hit reserve it prompted me back to the start. It’s a busy day, after a few attempts all time-slots were taken. Very disappointing experience!
A gem. Superb food, service, atmosphere and people. Find it, go, be delighted.
We shared the Black whole fish which was more than perfect.
It was one of THE MOST AWESOME dinners I have had in my life!
The Dabney's staff are very friendly and helpful. I really advise you to visit the place and try the steak!

Went for dinner and it was a great meal. We had the catfish dip, charred squash, scallop crudo, carrots, and chicken dumplings (pictured). Our favorite was the carrots and chicken but everything was wonderful. We can't wait to return!
I like to go to relive stress at the end of a long week. The smell of the wood fire and discreet staff make for a very relaxing experience.
Love this place so much! Will type more later about all the reasons why.
We had family style short rib and it was amazing. Service is best in town and absolutely love their decor.
Really enjoyed my experience here.  These service and ambiance were excellent and the food delicious and nicely plated. Small dishes are great to share. Reasonably priced.

My wife and I went to The Dabney for our first wedding anniversary and fell in love with it all. The food was fantastic, the atmosphere was on point, and the servers were passionate about what they were doing.
(Translated by Google) Everything was perfect. The service Home The dishes Flavors WOW!  (Original) Tout était parfait. Le service L’accueil Les plats Les saveurs WOW !
Simple perfection in every dish, every flavor, every pairing. Beautiful ambiance with the hearth ablaze, observant and never intrusive service. No place I've been does vegetables better.
We had a fabulous dinner.  Every dish was delicious with layers of flavors.  The catfish sliders were out of this world and the unique chicken and dumplings were fantastic.  Great service as well.

We had our dinner here on our 9th wedding anniversary. We enjoyed their delicious food but my favorite was the Chesapeake Rockfish and some red wine. The staff are very welcoming and attentive. Everything is just so clean and their washrooms smells amazing. Definitely one of the best meals I ever had in Washington.

Spectacular food.  The off menu catfish sliders, the charred squash, and salsify root each served as character rich primers to a spectacular sorghum-glazed beef short rib that cannot be described.  The words decadent, savory, luscious, opulent don't really capture the intensity of the herbs, flavor, and carmelized edges created by that massive hearth.  Wonderfully capped off with the sticky toffee pudding and chestnut mousse.  Deserves the Michelin nod.

Went to this place for a second time remembering it was really good, this time around I ordered the sugar toads which has a name im reluctant to get but decided to get them either way and I was blown away by how amazing they were. I also had an amazing Bartender that was recommending amazing drinks and by far this restaurant is hard to beat when it comes to customer service and quality of food. Plus there was a little treat after dinner and it topped it off really nice.

After reading the reviews I knew I had to stop by here. I spent about $350 worth of food and ever penny was worth it (compliments to the chef). My brother and I reserved a table and there wasn’t one thing we didn’t enjoy. The firewood, the ambiance, the servers were fantastic (we had Hannah I believe, thank you) and even the restrooms were all so beautiful. I enjoyed the decor and noted how the time for the food to come out was surprisingly quick. Wine selection is also very nice and the food is diverse, yet sticks to what the restaurant is. 10/10 will come back

Visited here with a friend around 9 PM on a Friday.  It took us some time to find the place so carefully review the map if it’s your first time visiting.  We couldn’t get a reservation on the website but were able to get seats at the bar by 9:30.  All plates were fresh and super delicious.  Bread was so yummy.  Also, excellent service and ambience.  Would love to come back!
Food is amazing, may be one of the best restaurants in the city. Good luck getting a seat though!
Excellent food! A range of american fare, on the lighter side rich in flavor and heft. It's not cheap, but you get what you pay for! ☆☆☆☆☆ Great Meal!
Tried this restaurant a few months ago and were delighted by all aspects.  Delicious food, wonderful service and warm, inviting atmosphere.  Can't wait to go back!

My husband and I stopped in on a Saturday night.  The staff was super attentive and insightful when picking food and drink selections.  We enjoyed the catfish sliders, charred carrots, chicken and dumplings, the short rib entree, and dessert.  The star of the show was the short rib.  Don't leave without sharing it.  Great cozy place to add to your dining out list!
Outstanding food served in a charming rustic restaurant that allows its guests to have a conversation without having to shout.
Loved every experience of it!!!
Reliably creative meals, cute back alley location.
Everything was good in this restaurant!
Our favorite restaurant in DC.
Great spot!
The servers were super attentive and polite and all of the food was amazing.
Best service great food
good service
Exceptional food and service
Hands down the best dinner I’ve ever had.
Excellent spot. Great food, atmosphere. Staff was flawless!

So amazing!! It was hard to get a reservation but well worth it! From the moment we stepped in, the hostesses were so welcoming. We were a couple minutes late and my husband was stuck at work. They sat us right away and even left a place sat for my husband if he could make it. Our waitress was knowledgeable and very kind giving us time to pick our selections w/out rushing us. The somm was lovely! Oh and the food was AMAZING! Very impressed. Would love to go back someday

A colleague from Toronto and I, from Los Angeles, stumbled upon this place looking for dinner before heading back to Baltimore. The space is beautifully put together, rather cozy and intimate. It elevated our dinning experience before we sat.  At the bar we were greeted by Megan behind the counter. She was most courteous and thorough presenting the menu to us. She'd continue to assist us through our meal with a level of warmth and attentiveness that made us feel at home.  We had the radishes, oysters, NY strip and swordfish. Each dish was meticulously put together with color and flavor to delight the palate. The food was, simply put, excellent.  I look forward to my next trip to the DC area just to experience this little gem one more time.
It s very delicious
Amazing! Totally recommend to anyone who loves a focus on fresh and seasonal. Every single dish was executed well.
The most amazing service and a scrumptiously delicious menu!
Most unique flavors, delicious food, friendly, sweet staff. Lively, yet cozy environment. Paloma gets 5 stars for service, knowledge of product and a pleasant, upbeat attitude
Incredible food. Well made, local ingredients prepared by very talented chefs and served by the nicest hospitality team in DC. Loved every minute of it
The food was awesome. The service fantastic. And the crew they had in the kitchen was unbelievable.
Amazing food and atmosphere! The staff is very friendly as well
Great vibe and wonderful staff. A+
Dabney is always great. Everything I've ever had here was delicious and service is super quick and friendly.
What is so great about this place? Everything!
Wow! A must! I really liked the open kitchen with the Hearth. Food was exceptional and reasonably priced ! We had such a great night.

Great food, great vibe, great staff. If you're on the waitlist for a seat or just want to grab a drink a small bite before dinner, definitely recommens The Dabney Cellar. Entrance is off of 9th St. Small intimate basement bar with a speakeasy vibe. If you don't finish your drinks and food before table is ready, they will bring everything up to your table for you!
Really spectacular food and superb service!

Awesome spot in DC. The service here is top notch. The team here does well to accommodate children surprisingly. It can be a bit pricey. This is definitely a place to go to show off to friends and family... Or perhaps a date.

This was one of the best experiences I've had in a restaurant. Loved the food, the service was so nice and friendly. The concept of a lot a dishes served small so you can try more than one or two dishes is great! Loved it! From now on when I visit Washington, I'll visit the dabney!

The food was good, the service was good but we walked out surprised they had a Michelin star.  The service was not what I would expect from a rated restaurant as the servers were disjointed and pushing drinks while pulling dishes before we were both done with our course.  We really enjoyed the scallops, grilled vegetables and the cornbread but the rest was just good.  So we enjoyed our meal but we expected something special like the other Michelin star restaurants in DC.

Honestly a great meal. Very interesting and delicious small plate selections at what ended up being a fairly reasonable price for what you were getting (it's not inexpensive...but it is worth it.) Cocktails  and alcohol selection were fantastic. We sat at the bar and the service was some of the best I've had in DC.

The Dabney was fantastic. Friendly and enthusiastic staff who care about food and your food experience. As a solo diner, I appreciated the modest wine by the glass menu. Cocktails looked inventive, fun, and thoughtful. One of them donated its proceeds to the hurricane dorian fund. The food was special. The catfish sandwich slider as a starter that warmed up the palate just right. The pullet egg was their own version of a mid-Atlantic bibimbap. Roasted vegetable plate showcased the regions green thump. Finished off with a local fernet. All was incredibly delicious. Would love to go back with 4 people and really let the menu sing.
Great food & excellent service
Best restaurant in DC hands down. Michelle star rated and great service!
Oysters, Quails and chicken are great!! That's why so many people are willing to line up for about 1 hour.

(Translated by Google) It is a charming place. Very nice service The food better than the coctails. Very rich tomato salad, quail and a vegetable salad. For dessert the brioche with cheese was great too.  (Original) Es un sitio con mucho encanto. Servicio muy agradable. La comida mejor que los coctails. Muy rica la ensalada de tomate, las codornices y una ensalada de vegetales. De postre la brioche con queso también estuvo genial.
Fabulous, innovative food. Loved the roast vegetables the best, although other things were also great. Sugar toads and catfish sliders were standouts.

- easy to see how they earned their Michelin Star-rating - mid-Atlantic comfort food in small-plates format (great for sharing!) - perfectly attentive, professional, and friendly staff and managers (THANK YOU for all the 'happy birthday' wishes!) - cozy, unpretentious, and romantic ambiance
Absolutely superb. If you only eat at one place in DC, make sure this is it.

Lovely ambiance with an open fire wood kitchen. The staff is attentive and the creative menu was delightful. It gets really busy and buzzy but not too loud to impede conversation. The only dish we didn’t like was the steak one, neither the cut or technique made it tender... it was too stringy and the veggies were too hard. My favorite dishes were the sweet potato rolls, the fluke and the baked Virginia.
This was hands down the best food I’ve had in DC. Great atmosphere, great cocktails delicious food. Somewhat pricey but definitely worth it.
Excellent all around plus stumptown !!!!! Amy is the best

Top notch service.. as expected.. but exceeded expectations. All of the servers were so personable and had so much personality. Our server shared with us details on the menu, specials, and her personal favorites. She didn’t rush us but as first timers there we also didn’t feel like we were left hanging stranded on an island.  All of the playing was beautiful and we went with about half of her recommendations, and half of what we thought sounded good. There wasn’t one dish that we didn’t like.  Let me go back to my exceeded expectations comment.. we had a tough time deciding on dessert.. much to my surprise they gifted us one of the two desired options AND brought us a glass of champagne to cap it all off.  I’ve been to several Michelin stared restaurants in the area, and this one truly made me feel special and made the dining experience unique, warm, and welcoming. I’d definitely go back! Great experience! The catfish sliders were AWESOME! Drinks Summer Harvest and 7th & H make the evening buzz feel Zen.😊
Fantastic food.

We celebrated our anniversary here last year and it couldn't have been more lovely. The service was exceptional, and the staff kindly gave us complimentary champagne to celebrate the occasion. The food was out of this world... my husband still raves about it. I love that the plates are small-ish so that we could sample so many things on the menu. Would definitely go back.
Yum

Cute restaurant set behind heavy wooden doors on an alley - yes, it’s on the actual alley- that is fast becoming a trendy European-style courtyard.  I dined with a group of four at 5:15 and everything was good. Fun ambience (it was packed at 5:15). Great service. Prompt with the drinks, a little slower with the food.  Just be aware that the plates are small and they encourage you to share, which doesn’t make much sense to me except that the prices are pretty high ($10-25 per small plate) so you probably won’t try many dishes unless you share.  Tip: try the fried catfish sliders which are not on the menu!
Great menu love the ambiance
Hard to get a reservation but easily my favorite restaurant in DC
Amazing restaurant!!!
My favorite restaurant in Blagden Alley. Amazing atmosphere, great food and friendly staff. You'll need a reservation-- they're always packed.

It was our first time in a Michelin star restaurant and we loved it!  There definitely were some flavors that we had never tasted in the US. Seeing cooks working in front of the open fire was a great experience and we enjoyed the original food associations.
Excellent friendly service, cozy setting but not stuffy, inventive food but familiar flavors. Can't wait to go back.

Loved the outdoor seating and vines 😍 Nice vibes too. All of the drinks were good (I ordered one and tasted a few) and the flavor of the simple appearing tomato pie was delightful. Hope to visit next time I’m in town.
My wife and I had the best anniversary dinner. From the food to the service, one of the best experiences we’ve had.
Great find in DC ! Vibrant atmosphere. Sharing plates style. Seared root salad amazing ! Also noteworthy the quail dish is a must try !
Good and solid Food.  Friendly stuff.  Not so great comfort but nice decoration.  Conclusion: Recommendation for an visit.

I’m always wary of restaurants that are touted as the “hip” places to be, but The Dabney did not disappoint. Fair warning... the cuisine is served as small plates that offer diners tastes of a variety of dishes so if you’re expecting a traditional menu of one-serving meals, this is not for you. But if you like variety with unique ingredients combined in creative ways, you’ll love the choices that are updated daily. The staff is knowledgeable and can offer recommendations based on your tastes. Expensive since about 4 plates is close to a full meal, but try it if you’re looking for something different.
This place is amazing!  The service, food, drinks were all fantastic and I can't wait to go back. Make sure to lick the bowl after you finish the quail dish.

When walking through an Alley becomes a whole experience... The Dabney is the perfect spot for a date or night out with the girls. It is located in an Alley turned Restaurant row. A unique concept that adds to the experience and is great for photos or a quick stroll to explore. The Dabney specializes in small plates and unique dishes with interesting combinations. However, somehow it all works together and becomes a perfect marriage of flavors in your mouth. You wont go wrong with the catfish sliders, which are absolutely delicious a must try that leave you wanting more. The broccoli crab, flank steak and potato salad. Each dish is presented with a nice little introduction that gets you excited about getting ready to taste your meal. Sarah took great care of us. She was attentive and answered all of our questions with great details. The decor is modern and there is a vibrant yet private feel and exclusive atmosphere. Although the restaurant isn't overly spacious each table setting is exclusive enough in that you feel alone and unbothered by others around you although every table is full and in great conversation.. When finished head next door to the Columbia Room and enjoy the rooftop deck and a couple of very eclectic drinks that you just have to try in order to understand.  #fallynsfoodieexcursions #thedabney #smallplatescanstillbegreat #alleyrestaurants #thecolumbiaroom
Second time returning here and it is absolutely yummy. I always make it a point to stop over here when I'm in town for business. Can't wait to be back!
Food was amazing. Service too.

While this place is a little hard to find, the food is worth the search. It was very close to the convention center. Menu is somewhat limited but the confit of chicken was to die for. Daphne was my bartender/server. Very friendly and professional. Decided to try a different wine and she was good enough just to give me a taste before I committed (which was great because I did NOT like my first choice). She then recommended another that was just right. Open kitchen, so you can see everyone working. Fancy cocktails with fresh herbs. You can eat both inside or outside. Only drawback was it was a little expensive (dinner for 1 person with 2 glasses of wine was $77)
Great food. Exceptional service.
One of the great treasures of creative cooking. Outstanding teamwork by ALL service staff! Wine list is superb! Stay away so I can continue to get a table!
Amazing!

CATFISH SLIDERS - SO DANG GOOD. Seriously.. get this. It was an off-menu item that they offered. The bread was so good, soft warm and sweet, the catfish had a nice crunch, and the pickled and mayo flavors just made this a package of delicousness. SCALLOP CRUDO - This reminded me of a ceviche. The scallops were super fresh and the texture was just right. Yum! HEARTH ROASTED SPRING VEGETABLES - I was on the fence about getting this dish at first, but am happy we opted for this. It was nice to have some greens and vegs before the last two heavy dishes. SOFTSHELL CRAB - This dish was good.. but it wasn't my absolute favorite. I just might not be crazy about softshell crab in general. The fact that it was deep fried and had a layer of some type of mayo sauce on top made this dish too rich for me. It was nice and crunchy. The green sauce (I think pureed pea shoot) helped to balance the richness a bit. GRILLED BEAVER CREEK QUAIL - There were no beavers harmed in the making of this dish.. lol This is a quail dish. The quail filet was cooked to a medium setting - never had poultry cooked medium before, but it worked out well! It was so tender and tasty. The claws also made me lol. I held onto them to eat the teeny quail thighs which were soo flavorful. BENNE, MILK & HONEY - This dessert had a variety of textures and flavors. There was definitely a sweet and savory thing going on. Loved loved the candied honey comb! We wanted to go with a dessert that is really different, and this fit the bill.

This is the second time we go to this place. The menu has changed since last time, but the food is still as good. It is a small plate type of place so we tried many of the options and they were all absolutely great.

I really love the carrots here! I know that sounds ridiculous, but they really are good!  The fried farro is good too. Service has always been good here. The grilled scallops is on of my favorite entrees I've ordered. This is definitely a cool place.
Amazing in every way. Relaxed atmosphere, incredible food.

My friend was able to snag a reservation for this place and of course I said yes. The Dabney is one of those spots that is so frequently raved about but so difficult to get into that I had never been.  From the time I entered the restaurant, I was immediately welcomed by warm service. The hostesses were very helpful and seated me right away.  The meal starts with the most wonderful bread and sorghum molasses butter. My friend and I could have probably eaten a whole loaf of this bread with the butter. SO good.  The fried oyster sliders were incredible, probably my favorite part of the meal. The sweet potato bun and the crunch of the oyster worked perfectly together.  We also ordered the scallop crudo which was just okay, honestly. I was kind of disappointed that our waitress had recommended this dish because it was a little bland. Not terrible but not mindblowingly good like the fried oyster sliders were.  For the entrees we ordered the quail and the chicken. The chicken left a little to be desired, honestly. The quail, however, was fantastic. The rice underneath the quail was actually quite good and I don't even really like rice!  Drinks were solid. I ordered a cocktail that had celery in it so the taste was pretty unique and on trend with the celery craze taking over America.  We didn't get to dessert so I'll save that for an updated review. I definitely want to come back!
Great people, food, wine and experience

Sat at the bar top with Megan, she was absolutely wonderful, gracious, professional and informative! We enjoyed multiple courses, all were delicious; however, The Carrots and The Bok Choy were knockouts!! Can’t wait to visit again! Yay!

We came here for our second time last night for a celebratory meal and could not have had a more lovely experience. We were so well looked after. The food was delectable, the drinks heavenly and the service encyclopaedic; the epitome of charm and diligence. Abby, at reception, squeezed us in and was cheerful and friendly. Ben who served us was a walking bible of good food and drink.  The crew at the Dabney should be proud of what they've created. The ambience is relaxing and warming (both times we've nearly been the last to leave). The cooking is simultaneously back to basics and cutting edge. Take a look at the wood-burning hearth in the open kitchen and watch the nonchalantly accomplished chefs moving the skillets and pans around in the flames and heat. The food is a perfect mix of tiptop ingredients, served in beautiful, colourful dishes woven together with imagination and creativity. This without being over-engineered and instead hearty and delicious. The team run the restaurant like clockwork but with the customers not the numbers first.  I think this might be DC's best restaurant and I don't say that lightly. Go there if and when you can, I'm not the first to realise this place is an absolute gem...

I can't say enough good things about this place.  The wait staff make you feel like you entered another world of warmth, acceptance and cooking tradecraft.  We went with 6 people, and with two nice bottles of wine and cocktails, our tab came to about 800, so unless you're rich, don't expect to go too often.  We got one of about everything on the menu, and while the meat dishes were cooked and flavored to perfection, the vegetables were insane - I didn't think carrots could that good, and I imagine brassicas must be pretty hard to cook since I have never seen them on the menu anywhere else.  Best dishes out of the 10 we tried: Catfish sliders on their homemade buns, grilled carrots, fried Chesapeake Sugar Toads, and charred greens.  Well done, Dabney!

I don't know what the restaurant is like, because it has THE WORST RESERVATION SYSTEM EVER. I had been waiting to make a reservation when they go live, but the system they use is buggy, and because of this I lost the reservation I had been waiting for days to make. Not acceptable in 2019!!

Hands down best restaurant in DC at the moment. All of the dishes are adaptations of Eastern shore standards and comfort food taken to a haute level with the freshest ingredients, the best preparation techniques, and the most well thought out plating and sauce/spice complements. The plates are small so if you are a group of 3 expect everyone to get one bite from a plate. Definitely order the off menu catfsh sliders. The beef spare rib (family style) is perfect for 4 people who are also getting 4 or 5 other plates or just 2 people who are doing maybe 1 or 2 other plates. Eastern shore dumplings were another highlight. Good cocktails round out the experience. Service was on point for a one star and if they up their plating game, work on combining more textures into each dish, and add a few waitstaff to each table then they will get a second star in the near future.
Bread is delicious! Food is very good. Somewhat overpriced but service was also good although a little slow at times.

The atmosphere and the service was great.  It was very cozy and the fire in the kitchen made it seem like we were in an old farm house.  The food was ok at best, I will go back for the atmosphere but hoping it will be a different menu.

Really fantastic staff and the food was AMAZING!!! You of course have to get the sugar toads, but I had their daily specisl which was a catfish slider (breaded and cooked to perfection. Both food paired beautifully with their dry cider. I alao loved the ambiance of the place. Overall a great experience!

The Dabney is the whole package. On my visit, everything from the food to the service to the lighting and the temperature of the dining room was perfect. I love their concept of small plates as it allowed us to sample a wide variety of dishes. By far, the gem of the evening was the blue crab... The flavor and delicate texture are almost indescribable in their perfection. The pacing of the dishes was excellent, and the waitstaff were extremely attentive and solicitous. Of course, the food was the main event, but I was pleasantly surprised that I couldn't find a single thing to critique about this place. Bathrooms? Spotless. Music? Tasteful and not too loud. Lighting? Romantic but not too dark. Decor? Impecable (and seasonal). Temperature? Ideal (I'm usually too cold at restaurants, but I was actually able to send my coat to coat check here and I didn't miss it one bit!)

Wonderful experience with The Dabney. I did not eat there but reserved a table for 2 for my parent’s anniversary. I called ahead to leave my payment information so that the meal was taken care of. My parents had a wonderful time. When they arrived, glasses of chapagme were brought to their table and the menus had a “Happy anniversary” from the chef! The restaurant is tucked away in a cobblestoned side street and you wouldn’t know it was there if you weren’t looking for it. The interior is beautiful. What’s special about the Dabney is that they use a big wood fire so that the food has a certain smokey quality that cannot be produced in the home kitchen. My parents said the food was terrific! This is an ideal place to go for a special occasion. Just be sure to go online and reserve a table, they fill up fast!
Esquisite food! Great service? Needs a dessert wine by the glass and an expresso machine.
Amazing food, staff is incredible and the attention to detail is next to none. 5 stars all the way highly recommend to anyone to check this place out!

The Dabney is an experience that lives up to the hype. The restaurant is a study in balance and love of craft. The food is simple, but executed perfectly. Highlighting ingredients and recipies of the Chesapeake and mid-Atlantic, the food is satisfying without being heavy, delicate without being insubstantial. The flavors are absolutely luscious. The bar also serves up some classic and original delights. The waitstaff are sweetly enthusiastic, warm, and welcoming without being overbearing or energy-draining. The atmosphere is cosy, but not too dim. The open fire which the kitchen uses to cook many dishes sets off the room beautifully. The open kitchen is a delight to watch, as everyone plays their role with precision and grace. Notably, the kitchen feels relaxed and collegial; no manufactured display of high tension, only a practiced confidence and a deep respect for the food. They share love, here. Reservations are recommended, but you could sneak in to the bar by yourself or one companion without too much fuss most weeknights.

Did not live up to expectations. The service, atmosphere, and cocktails were excellent, but the food and wine was just okay. The radish appetizers was literally a small bowl of radishes served with butter. The fried oysters were three tiny oysters with a plate of sliced radishes. The lobster was completely underwhelming. The bright spots were the blue crab and pork. We tried several red wines, but none of them did much for us. The house cocktails were interesting and delicious.
One of the best meals I've ever experienced.  Incredible staff mixed with an innovative and creative menu with stunning presentation.  Well worth the price of admission.

Make reservations ASAP. This is an amazing experience. The menu changes each night, all small plate items each with their own unique flavors. Service was spot on, situated in an alley that once served access to carriages of DC elites. The food is prepared over wood ambers allowing the chefs to delicately cook each item.
Divine. Waitstaff was great, and guided us in our selection for a great culinary experience. Drinks were great.

We couldn’t get a reservation for the place, but a walk in on Tuesday worked. We had to wait for about an hour (theres bars next door), but we were given a table instead of a place at the bar, which was nice. The food was lovely, we liked everything we tried, but the brassicas and the sweet potato bread pudding were phenomenal. We felt that the sugar toads could have been more flavorful, it was not a bad dish, but it just didn’t stand up to how impressive everything else was. Check came to $179 for a super generous meal for two people, including 3 drinks.

I have been to The Dabney a couple times and it has some of the most delicious food I've ever eaten. Here are the items I tried (Sorry, didn't get pictures of everything): 1. St. Malachi Cheese: A charred cracker with cheese, honey, and fruit. Overall it was a good combination, but nothing that blew me away. The char on the cracker was the main taste that came forward.  2. Crispy Pig Ear Lettuce Wraps: The pig ears taste like perfectly crispy bacon, and the wraps bring a very delicious combination of savory from the pig ear and freshness from the lettuce and vinaigrette.  3. Maryland Blue Crab: Absolutely amazing, the crab with the texture and tartness of the walnuts and apples is divine. I could eat 5 orders of this.  4. Winter Squash: One of the most delicious vegetable dishes I've ever eaten. The greens complement the nice hearty flavor of the squash.  5. Charred Carrots: The carrots are always sweet, savory, and tasty. The only problem with these is sometimes the cuts are a little uneven so the center of the bigger pieces are slightly undercooked.  6. Grilled Scallops: If you love scallops, you will love these. Cooked with a chewy center and crisp on the outside.  7. Winter Radishes & Fried Oysters: Definitely one of the best looking dishes I ordered. The crispy oysters work perfectly with the tart radishes. However, you do end up with 80% radishes, which can be a little too tart on their own.  8. Foie Gras Biscuit: The foie gras had a creamy texture, and has a very strong savory flavor which pairs nicely with the sweet sauce on the biscuit.  9. Chesapeake Rockfish: I would definitely be sure to get this dish. Every element on this dish works perfectly together, from the two different sauces to the winter spice crumble. One of the more complicated dishes they make, and every part is worth the effort.  10. Spicy Lobster and Grits: Awesome buttery lobster, and a side of creamy grits. I can't ask for more.  11. Autumn Olive Farms Pork: The unassuming black pepper mash they put next to the pork can surprise you with the level of spice concentrated in it. Everything on the dish nicely complements the juicy and tender pork.  12. Bourbon Brown Sugar Sundae: The alcohol used in this dessert is not overpowering, and the sweetness of this dessert is nicely accented with the marshmallows and candied ginger.
This place was good. Just not great for me. The catfish slider was amazing that night. The service was excellent. I've just had a lot of different really good food, and therefore I'm pretty picky.

My wife and I came here for our 8 year anniversary. She is a professional chef and we have eaten at Michelin star restaurants all around the world.  This was the absolute best dining experience of our lives. It was probably the most helpful staff ever. The service was impeccable and the food was perfect. The chef sent over multiple dishes for us to try and made the evening unforgettable.  I look forward to when they get more stars. I cannot rave about this place enough. This is worth traveling far to eat here.
Yes.  The food was perfect.  The service was wonderful as well. Passionate and knowledgeable - like they truly cared about us and what they were serving.  Attentive but not pushy.

Unbelievable – the Dabney is amazing. Our server Katie, and managers Alex and Erica went above and beyond to make our experiences a wonderful one. The food was delicious, the staff was inviting, the ambience was warm and welcoming. You will not regret going to this restaurant!
Amazing experience! Not just a meal but an experience! My tastebuds are euphoric. The most hygge atmosphere I've experienced lately as well. Service like eating at a friend's home.  So welcoming.

The food and service were top notch. The Bar seating is first come first serve but I recommend making a reservation (we had to make ours two weeks in advance-yes they fill up that quickly). Our server Jessie was amazing along with the whole staff. Our waters were always filled and she was very attentive and the cocktails were made very well and in a way that you could actually taste the flavors of the liquor and herbs and not just a sugary concoction. I recommend to ask your server for recommendations on drinks if you're not sure on what to try. It's a short walk from the yellow/green line and walking distance to Chinatown Gallery Place. Would recommend to anyone to come and enjoy an evening.

Amazing food, everything is made to order, so all dishes are always the best quality and plated perfectly.  Some of the dishes sound a little plain, but after tasting them you taste how well all the ingredients of each dish work together. Every dish I had there was excellent, so I dont think you could pick wrong on anything. I would recommend dessert as well, had the apple crumble and it was tasty.
Incredible!!

Fantastic!
The best dinner I ever ate. Every dish was an experience. Cosy atmosphere. Needs advance booking.

Great experience. Highlight dishes were the fried rockfish sandwich on a homemade sweet potato roll, the charred vegetable and grain salad and the foie gras mousse. Service was exceptional and made us feel super welcome.

We enjoyed a great anniversary dinner at The Dabney! The Seven Sisters cheese plate and the Succotash were absolutely phenomenal! The atmosphere is great and they situate their tables a comfortable distance apart for the best dining experience possible. Watching food cooked over an open fire is always a delightful experience.
Absolutely amazing! Aesthetically pleasing! Quail was underwhelming, but everything thing else was above and beyond expectations!!!

Their open kitchen featuring a roaring wood fire combined with proficient service make this Michelin 🌟 restaurant a must dining experience.

I adored the wait staff- funny and hyper-personable (way to go Liz!). I really enjoyed the bread and sorghum jars. Other than that, the food quality is good and solid. Nothing really stood out as exceptionally amazing over or under as each dish was presented well and had unique flavors.

This wasn't just a great meal. This was a great experience. There was a sense of passion, pride and caring that permeates the atmosphere of The Dabney.  Everyone that we interacted with demonstrated that they really cared about our experience.  Their team really is fantastic.  The snacks, small plates and the family style choices are perfect for sharing and provide a community feeling.  We ordered 3 snacks,  a few small plates, the main, and all of the sides.  There wasn't a single misstep in presentation or taste. Everything seemed to belong together.  Pacing was great, never rushed or left waiting. Flavors were absolutely amazing. Cocktails were outstanding. There was some serious skill on display from the mixologist.  Very nice wine list as well.  We finished with 2 great desserts and 2 fine ports.  There aren't enough adjectives to describe the experience.  Simply put, one of the finest dining experiences I've ever had.  If you have the chance to go, do not pass it up.  Go hungry, and try everything. You will not be disappointed.  If anyone from the team at The Dabney reads this, thank you very much for a truly fantastic experience.

I loved the look and feel of this restaurant. Serious about the food, but casual and comfortable. The lighting is lovely. The acoustics were great -- guests want to be able to hear each other at dinner and so many places don't get this right. The sound was good especially given we were near the open kitchen which added theater to our dining experience but didn't intrude. Very attentive service.  The rolls for the catfish sliders were whispering from across the room when I spied them on the slide in the kitchen area. They didn't disappoint. The food was beautifully styled and delicious. We almost ordered a second tuna Crudo. A simple pea  and mint spread was complex and served with warm grilled pita. The charred raddicchio don't sound that appetizing but it was one of the best dishes. I loved the look of the beet dish and the flavor, but the texture of the uncooked beets against the cooked beets didn't work for me  We had the lamb which was perfectly seasoned and roasted and had a simple but perfect tomato salad and a grain dish that I loved but can't recall the details of. We had at least half the dishes on the menu so my palate was happily overwhelmed.  The desserts didn't dazzle as much as the other dishes. They seemed a little stingy size wise but that gave us more room to eat second dessert at Butter cream.  This was probably the best meal I've eaten in DC... ever.
Great ambiance, great and knowledgeable host. Food tasty although not overly impressed. Will try again and recommend
One of my favorite places to eat in DC!
So good !
I'd recommend going, this place is excellent and the service is amazing. The food is over the top, I loved everything I ate.
Chick-fil-A is like 1 billion times better
Excellent

Outstanding meal, outstanding service,  outstanding standards for a  restaurant. Excellent chef. Certainly worth the one star Michelin rating. Food is fresh and staff is highly trained to provide impeccable service.

We had such an amazing time. Everything we ordered was expertly designed and crafted. We ordered like 6 small things and every one was absolutely awesome. We lucked out and got a seat at the bar(rarely are there seats available). Our bartender was so helpful and great. They made the dishes dairy free for my wife and it was still outstanding. And don't forget desert! So tasty.

I don't even know where to begin. This place was phenomenal. From the moment I called to place a reservation to the moment we left we treated amazing. The service was top of the line. Then on top of amazing service, the food was almost literally to die for. The catfish slider was a perfect way to start dinner. It was a great size and very yummy. The hot sauce paired wonderfully with the citrus sauce. The softshell crab was a must order. It blew me away. I didn't expect it to be so amazing. Then as a main dish we ordered the short rib, which was oh so yummy. It's a lot of food but worth it. The short ribs are unreasonably tender, and the seasoning is sort of sweet which was very unexpected, but extra delicious.

We started in the wine bar. It was amazing. Great, smallish wine list and some thoughtful, light small plates.  We moved to the restaurant and had the crab dish. Delicious. Light on mint, bold flavor. Wine list was heavy on Italian and Spanish wines - not an issue, but I typically prefer something less thin, with filler body.  We got the short rib and acoutrement. Short ribs were good and crispy but over seasoned. The quinoa has too much soy, but I get how they were trying to match the short ribs in flavor. Tomato salad was basic but refreshing, especially when paired with such heavy, over seasoned dishes. We didn’t get dessert (too full)  I’d return, but be more thoughtful of our structute of the meal.
Great drinks. Fun atmosphere. Definitely pricey but a good addition to the Blagden Alley
One of my top favorite restaurants in DC, the food is always delicious, nothing to avoid on this menu and the service is always great!

'Twas a treat! Nearly every dish was excellent. It's a warm inviting establishment which is backlit by a glowing hearth bursting with flames. Many of the dishes are prepared by that aforementioned woodfire. Those that are cooked by wood …
Best place ever
Unbelievable food, fantastic atmosphere
Great food. American-World Cuisine in a modest fusion style. Extremely friendly service. Well deserved M-Star!

My wife and I have now been to The Dabney twice, most recently this weekend for our anniversary.  It's our new favorite restaurant in DC.  The ambiance, service and (most importantly) the food is absolutely superb.  It's hard to get a table, but if you can, there's no reason not to eat here.  The DC food scene has gotten ridiculously good over the 11 years I've lived here, and, in my opinion, The Dabney is the top of them all.

Shared a great meal here with family. Every single dish that came out was marvelous and the server was excellent both at noticing our every need and also helping us select a great wine. Food was incredible, great atmosphere, and good company. What more could one ask for? 5-star experience.

One of the best DC dining experiences. It’s easy to understand why it’s earned a Michelin star.  This isn’t your normal farm-to-table. Every single dish we ordered had a unique, authentic taste. Everything tastes so fresh and was flavored exceptionally well. The carrot salad, chicken and dumplings, bread with lard were all amazing.  Getting a reservation is the most frustrating part 😊
Easily one of my favorite restaurants. The establishment is amazing and the menu is very good.
An exceptional dining experience the first time. Very tough to get seats, so the second time we sat at the bar.  Still great.

Pros: Beautiful decor, loved watching the chefs at work. Was like a well oiled machine.  Cons: While the food presented well the flavors were forgettable. Watching other tables, their portion control also needed some work. For price point, and how The Dabney presents itself, I expected better.

The Dabney is a well reviewed restaurant featuring small plates.  I found the staff to be very friendly and efficient.  My waitress suggested I try 3 small plates but I selected only two.  Here is where the costs can add up very quickly when you add wine or a cocktail or two. The wines I selected were very good and included a nice mix.  The plates were good but did not really knock me off my feet but I will likely go again since my selection was limited.
Slowly becoming my favorite special occasion place.
We were able to enjoy dinner out on the patio right before a downpour. Service was great. My favorite part of the meal was the charred lettuce salad - nice mix of textures and flavors.
Wow. Everything was amazing. I don't think I can really say much more. If you want to impress someone no matter how much of a foodie they are, take them here.

For a while now, I've been trying to get a reservation at The Dabney downtown and yesterday for my birthday I was lucky enough to have that happen.  My hubby took me for an amazing experience.  The food was delicious with the unusual combinations you would never think of. They cook their food using an open wood-burning kitchen.  I watched as they added more wood, fan the fire, poke the wood to make the perfect amount of fire to cook with. The restaurant is a very pricey but worth it for the experience.  At the end of the meal, they brought us 2 glasses of bubbly compliments of the house and after dessert they brought us what they call 2nd dessert a pair of freshly baked gingersnaps.  The food and the staff were amazing.  Thank you Dabney for helping us celebrate my birthday in style!
Superb food and service

My favorite restaurant I've been to in DC. What a perfect meal from food to ambiance to service, especially for the price. Dishes are larger than tapas but smaller than full-size entrees. The waitress's recommendation of 2-3 dishes per person was appropriate. Each dish was creative and attended to details. Dabney did not need to win attention from your palate with excessive oil or salt like many other  restaurants (e.g. Tail Up Goat). The dishes were full of flavors, distinctive while harmonious. Dabney wasn't trying to be very fancy or theatrical like a lot of two or three stars places , but if the taste matters most to you, this is the place to go. Excellent selection of wines as well (not that they collect an expensive list , but they actually "select" good-value ones for you within the small menu). I can't wait to come back again.
Pricey but delicious.

Dine near the open kitchen and word burning hearth. Locally sourced food with an exquisite variety of small plates and main course options. Put the Dabney on your list of must go-to restaurants. Also plan to visit the Dabney cellar for a large selection of wine, raw bar and sharable plates.
It really is that good.
Amazing!
Excellent staff, delicious food, great atmosphere for a dinner out.
Better than you heard. Wow!
Great food. Great service.
(Translated by Google) Best restaurant in DMV.  (Original) Best restaurant in DMV.

We have been 4 times now, and never had a bad dish. I will say that it is actually better now than when it first opened. This time we had the sweet potato roll with catfish, celery root dish, sweet potato dish, steak and pork. Then the black bass family style dish with red peas, bitter greens and salad.  The butterscotch tart dessert was outstanding, and so was the ice cream sundae.
Awesomeness. Service was great. Food even better. How many "wow" moments can one have in one meal? Great stuff.

Love, Love, Loved it! Every single thing we ordered was fantastic, an almost impossible feat at a small plates restaurant. The atmosphere and service were great too. It can be very hard to get into though, so plan ahead.

My wife and I showed up as the Dabney opened on Sunday night. We were quickly sat at a high top in the bar area. The mixed drinks were excellent and priced relatively cheap for a Michelin rated restaurant ($13-15). We proceeded to have a …
Perfect! It was ,simply, perfect. Service, food, menu, drinks, hostess, even the washrooms are Perfect!!!!
Uhhhh-mazing, get everything! There's also a cute wine bar in the basement.

I came here for my birthday and it was one of the best meals I've ever had in D.C. Their small plates are slightly larger than typical "small plates" and every dish was bursting with flavor. A couple of stand out items include the scallop crudo, caramelized onion toast, and fried sugar toads (not actual toads, fyi). The ambiance is really cozy and open kitchen concept with the blazing fire was fun to watch.
This place is fantastic..

A good restaurant is marked by it's consistency to bring you good food. This place is way too hit or miss. The food was way off and loaded with all of the trappings of wealth by failing to make me feel like my money was well spent. Chick fil a deserves more for making me feel like I got what I paid for. Service was great.
One of my favorite restaurants in the city.  Farm to table, local great-tasting fare in a lovely setting.  Drinks are awesome as well.  Very well recommended.
Great food, great service, good wine and nice venue.

Great location, nice atmosphere, beautiful cocktails, reasonable price, but the food doesn't deserve a Michelin star in my opinion. The taste was good, but not refined. It lacks balance and the products are covered by too much heavy sauce and toppings.

Great service and dessert but exquisite ingredients were overwhelmed by sauces, toppings, etc.  Exquisite local foodstuffs like Sugar Toads, Virginia Scallops, foie gras were overwhelmed by sauces and extras, hiding their unique flavor. I couldn't taste the sweet flavor of the Sugar Toads for the thick overly sweet breading, and the sauce on the scallops masked their mineral taste.  Service was excellent for both food and wine. The outstanding  dessert was the highlight of the meal; I'd follow the pastry chef anywhere she goes.  Overall a disappointing experience for a place I've heard so much about, and which takes pride in sourcing unusual local ingredients; don't think I'll return. :-(
Everything here is amazing. Great atmosphere! The Duck and smoked sweet potatoes are awesome! Don't leave without trying the desserts. They were mind blowing!

The Dabney is a delight from start to finish. As soon as you walk in you see the large fire that they've become known for over which they prepare almost everything that comes to your table. Even if you can't get one of the must have reservations, try your luck at getting a seat at the bar where you can order the full menu. Defer to your server as many of the menu items shift. The breads are all lovely, the sliders are large, and everything is best enjoyed shared with a friend or four. All of the service lives up to the hype (and price tag). Drinks are unique and fun - have an extra one here instead of going to the much talked about neighbor, Columbia Room. These are a better value in a far better space.
Creative local and seasonal menus! The vegetable courses are a must!

Amazing experience at The Dabneys. Despite us making reservations for the wrong night, the super friendly and extra helpful staff managed to get us a table. The setting with the open kitchen and the huge fireplace is beautiful and the wine selection is perfect. But the best part was the food!! Scallops and leeks in an amazing sauce. Wonderful vegetables, fresh, tasty and served with the perfect match if herbs and spices. And there was the quail... I don't remember what were the spices, but I do remember this was the best quail I ever had. Tender, juicy and so tasty I didn't want it to end. Will definitely be back next time in in D. C. BRAVO au chef et son équipe
Phenomenal food, drinks, and service. I would definitely return.
a "must-eat" restaurant for any foodie visiting or residing in DC
Beautiful decor and a cozy feel with fresh ingredients and creative pairings with beautiful dishes. Well sourced menu and a wine list that offers many great options.
Wow. Great decor, great staff, and superb food. Yes, there will be things on the menu you may not like, they are amazing dishes and drinks that have layers of flavor. Make a reservation!

UPDATED REVIEW:  It’s been a year since I last went to The Dabney (and gave it 5 stars, old review below), and I’m afraid I have to revise it down to 3 stars.  Perhaps it’s Michelin arrogance, but the standard and service have dropped markedly. The menu on the day was uneventful and the portions have been sized down. Suddenly you find yourself spending over $100 per person for a number of shared plates with an unsatisfied appetite. The Dabney is the type of restaurant that will now charge you $15 for lettuce, and market fois gras and toast as modern cuisine, while offering three items on a plate for two people (really?).  I took a friend from out of town to The Dabney to impress her - we left unimpressed.  REVIEW OCT 2016:  Love, love, love this place. Hands down one of the best restaurants I've been to in DC thus far. A total experience: excellent service, excellent ambiance, excellent setting. The food was exquisite, small plates but absolutely delicious. That they're small plates encourages you to order a few plates, thus getting a wide taste of the menu. Well deserved of the Michelin rating.

An absolutely delightful dining experience! The warm hearth and rustic setting sets a beautiful stage and the rotating menu always features the freshest available ingredients. Mixing and matching between the small plates and large plates gives you the best bang for your buck. The roast duck, smoked squash and foie grois biscuit were some of the highlights! Hopefully they'll still be on the menu when I go back.
One of our favorite spots in DC!  Definitely add this one to your list.

This is a fantastic restaurant for a special occasion. The waitstaff is excellent, and the food is incredible. My girlfriend and I tried five dishes and a dessert, and two of the dishes were perfect, while the others were *better* than I could have imagined. We can't wait to go back. A reservation is highly recommended, and should be made well in advance.
